wiki.summary: "Low Life" is a song by American hip hop recording artist Future, featuring Canadian singer The Weeknd. It was released on March 1, 2016, as the lead single from Future's fourth studio album, Evol (2016). The song was written by Future, Metro Boomin, The Weeknd and DaHeala. The song was produced by Metro Boomin and Ben Billions, with co-production by The Weeknd and additonal production by DaHeala. Read more on Last.fm.
